      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ARCADIAN WIZARD (2) started at long odds last time but ran well above expectations, breaking through for a maiden win by 1.75 lengths at Hobart over 461m (25.99). Drawn well off an inside draw. Yet to win at the journey but has run some good races. Can make it two on the bounce. RAVING LUNATIC (4) held his own to the line last start and filled a minor placing, beaten only 1.75 lengths (26.12) behind ARCADIAN WIZARD at Hobart. Leading player again. BUCKLE UP RAE (1) copped a check in the run and finished a well held 8 lengths third (30.81) last time in a Grade 5 at this track over 515m. Rates a key player. THAT'S WHEN (3) can fill a top-three spot.",
